	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This is in addition to my last post. <BR>
<BR>
Since this is a strategy guide, here's something else that all bards MUST know.<BR>
<BR>
Learn the strengths of ALL classes! This is extremely important so that you can be the most effecient when you are grouping. Bards are the only class than can do a little of everything, including selos's, haste, heal, buff (resistances) levitate, invis your party; or melee, slow, DoT,  DD, Mez, charm, lull your pulls. But every class that specializes in these areas DOES IT BETTER THAN YOU. So if you have a druid, don't sing your binding song and slow your target. It doesn't last as long, does no damage, and OVERRIDES the druids snare. So does our levitate song. If you are somewhere where levitate is needed and you have a caster with it (i.e. Mage, druid) and are grouped DON'T SING IT. Again you will override it and when your party is too far away will fall (into the water/lava/slippery floor/holes) If you are in a group with an enchanter, don't try to mex or charm, let the enchanter do it. THey can do it MUCH better than you and will last alot longer. If you have all tanks, why would you have a mana song memmed? Have something else that will benefit the group. If you are the puller, but have tanks in your group (bards are the BEST pullers besides monks maybe) don't worry about having damage songs, have Haste/STR/mana (if you have casters) memmed with your lull and one DoT or DD to pull with. <BR>
<BR>
It's not important that you learn how to play these other classes though, so don't get to overwhelmed &lt;:). Just know what your party can and can't do so you can fill in the weaknesses. Since we have SO many abilities, that's what we do.<BR>
<BR>
And if you are the enchanter (you are the one mezzing and fearing and charming) make sure you announce it! Tanks really hate it when you charm something and then they try to hit it LOL. So do casters though because it wastes mana. BUT you also MUST announce it so the healer will watch your health especially. We don't get nearly the hit points of warriors nor the defensive abilities of the other hybirds, so the healer will be healing you more than the others because of this (Charm mem wipes the mob but creates UBER hate for you when it wears off, and mez creates alot of hate for you too. Think about this: 4 mobs, 3 mezzed and killing one. the mez wears off in 9 seconds, who are those other 3 going to go for? Mez again you say? what if one resists, or worse yet all 3? equals dead bard awaiting rez.) <BR>
<BR>
So learn your friends classes. and if you don't know, ask them. People will usually RAVE about their class and what they are good at, and what they are not so good at. <BR>
<BR>
Good Luck, my fellow bards :). If you are on the Innoruuk Server, send me a tell. I can talk forever about my favorite class.<BR>
<BR>
Rinaya Sweettone, Bard of the 40th Song<BR>
Doves of Truth<BR>
Innoruuk Server
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
