	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I'm really surprised that the majority of posts (at least the most recent ones) are done by people who are still fairly new to the class (i.e. pre-30) You all haven't seen soloing yet! You have all done the Selo's/bellow/heal combo right? Well at 40, I can choose that, or Selo's with 2 different DoTs, or charm kiting! Charm kiting is charming a mob while running at the same time. You actually need =2 mobs to do this. Charm one and then pull another by letting it hit you or using a damage song. your pet will now attack and the mob you are fighting will attack your pet. Now, you have to re charm every 9 secs, and charm the same mob! The one you are fighting will hate your pet more than you and you only need to get attacked (not hit necessarily) once for your pet to attack. If you've pulled 2 equal mobs, wait until the first one is dead, then kite the one you were charming. You get half exp for the first one (pet did most of the damage) and full exp for the second (each charm is also a memory wipe)! Then sit and heal and you're ready to do it again. After you get to 40 you might have to use your lvl 39 (I think) charm which uses mana, so you can't charm forever without medding too. <BR>
<BR>
Now, granted you can't do this until you get your first charm, and make sure you have alot of CHA (mine is 134) so it doesn't get resisted as much. But if you have heard that Bards can't solo past 30, it's a lie! They can!<BR>
<BR>
P.S. If you go to places like the Eastern Wastes, use a mammoth or a rhino as your pet. These guys hit hard, have ALOT of hit points, and you can kill 3-4 lesser things with one pet! Plus they're fairly stupid and are easily charmed. (3-4 snow cougars with one mammoth is nice, especially if one drops an earring!) <BR>
<BR>
So play with it. You'll learn your own strategy, and if you get to low of health you can always run to the zone with your drum equipped, because nothing can catch you! <BR>
<BR>
Be safe, my fellow Bards! The Jam Session has just begun!<BR>
<BR>
Rinaya Sweettone, Bard of the 40th Song<BR>
Doves of Truth<BR>
Innoruuk Server
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
